---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Daniel Kim, focusing on the intersection of RL, systems, and theory."
>
  <h1>About Me</h1>
  <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); max-width: 38rem;">
    I am a researcher exploring the intersection of theoretical statistics, computer systems, and reinforcement learning. My goal is to build intelligent agents that are both mathematically grounded and computationally efficient.
  </p>

  <div class="svg-container" style="margin: 4rem 0; display: flex; justify-content: center; overflow: visible;">
    <svg width="400" height="400" viewBox="0 0 400 400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <defs>
        <!-- Gradients for lines -->
        <linearGradient id="line-top-center" x1="200" y1="50" x2="200" y2="200">
          <stop offset="0%" stop-color="var(--color-accent)" stop-opacity="0.8"/>
          <stop offset="100%" stop-color="var(--color-text-primary)" stop-opacity="0.2"/>
        </linearGradient>
        <linearGradient id="line-bl-center" x1="79" y1="270" x2="200" y2="200">
          <stop offset="0%" stop-color="var(--color-accent)" stop-opacity="0.8"/>
          <stop offset="100%" stop-color="var(--color-text-primary)" stop-opacity="0.2"/>
        </linearGradient>
        <linearGradient id="line-br-center" x1="321" y1="270" x2="200" y2="200">
          <stop offset="0%" stop-color="var(--color-accent)" stop-opacity="0.8"/>
          <stop offset="100%" stop-color="var(--color-text-primary)" stop-opacity="0.2"/>
        </linearGradient>
        
        <!-- Triangle border gradient -->
        <linearGradient id="triangle-border" x1="200" y1="60" x2="200" y2="270">
          <stop offset="0%" stop-color="var(--color-border)" stop-opacity="0.8"/>
          <stop offset="100%" stop-color="var(--color-border-light)" stop-opacity="0.4"/>
        </linearGradient>

        <!-- Arrowhead markers -->
        <marker id="arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--color-border)" />
        </marker>
      </defs>

      <!-- Background Triangle with bi-directional arrows -->
      <!-- Shrunk slightly so arrows don't overlap nodes -->
      <line x1="180" y1="85" x2="95" y2="235" stroke="url(#triangle-border)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />
      <line x1="110" y1="270" x2="290" y2="270" stroke="url(#triangle-border)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />
      <line x1="305" y1="235" x2="220" y2="85" stroke="url(#triangle-border)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />

      <!-- Connecting Lines to Center -->
      <line x1="200" y1="60" x2="200" y2="200" stroke="url(#line-top-center)" stroke-width="2" />
      <line x1="79" y1="270" x2="200" y2="200" stroke="url(#line-bl-center)" stroke-width="2" />
      <line x1="321" y1="270" x2="200" y2="200" stroke="url(#line-br-center)" stroke-width="2" />

      <!-- Nodes -->
      <!-- Center Node: Daniel Kim -->
      <g>
        <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="28" fill="var(--color-surface)" stroke="var(--color-text-primary)" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="200" y="196" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">Daniel</text>
        <text x="200" y="210" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">Kim</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Top Node: Stats (Theory) -->
      <g style="cursor: help;">
        <title>Rigorous Statistical Inference</title>
        <circle cx="200" cy="60" r="32" fill="var(--color-bg)" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="200" y="56" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">Stats</text>
        <text x="200" y="70" font-family="var(--font-serif)" font-size="10" font-style="italic" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">(Theory)</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Bottom-Left Node: CS (System) -->
      <g style="cursor: help;">
        <title>High-performance Systems</title>
        <circle cx="79" cy="270" r="32" fill="var(--color-bg)" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="79" y="266" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">CS</text>
        <text x="79" y="280" font-family="var(--font-serif)" font-size="10" font-style="italic" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">(System)</text>
      </g>

      <!-- Bottom-Right Node: RL (Domain) -->
      <g style="cursor: help;">
        <title>Optimal Sequential Decisions</title>
        <circle cx="321" cy="270" r="32" fill="var(--color-bg)" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="321" y="266" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">RL</text>
        <text x="321" y="280" font-family="var(--font-serif)" font-size="10" font-style="italic" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">(Domain)</text>
      </g>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <h2>Background</h2>
  <p>
    The triangle above illustrates my core philosophy. To solve complex problems in reinforcement learning, one must not only understand the underlying mathematical theory (Statistics & Probability) but also how to engineer robust and scalable systems (Computer Science). The domain of RL is where these two pillars converge.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
